pageContext.claim: “So, you know Ron's been a friend of mine for a long time. He was a Congressman. He did an incredible job, always protecting me from the Russia witch hunt and beyond, with these guys with Matt and everybody. He'd be up an incredible race, and then, he ran against the Democrat, who is supposed to be unbeatable. He got beaten badly, and now, this is one of the most popular Governors.”
pageContext.analysis: Ron DeSantis, the governor of Florida, ran against Andrew Gillum, the mayor of Tallahassee. Gillum was not considered "unbeatable." It was always supposed to be close, hard-fought race. DeSantis won by 34,000 votes, a margin of 0.4%.
